<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,475,789]" pageId="3" pageNumber="581">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,368,618,644]" pageId="3" pageNumber="581">Identification.</emphasis>
This species was identified from descriptions and illustrations found in the revision by 
<bibRefCitation author="Holzenthal, R. W. &amp; Blahnik, R. J." pageId="3" pageNumber="581" pagination="1 - 37" refId="ref5850" refString="Holzenthal, R. W. &amp; Blahnik, R. J. (2006) The caddisfly genus Protoptila in Costa Rica (Trichoptera: Glossosomatidae). Zootaxa, 1197, 1 - 37." type="journal article" year="2006">Holzenthal &amp; Blahnik (2006)</bibRefCitation>
. The phallicata of this species is distinctively shaped, appearing wide preapically in lateral view and narrow basally in dorsoventral view. Additional characters, such as the elongate, apically bifurcate processes of tergum X, the shape of the paramere spine, and the elongate, narrowed ventral apex of sternum VIII assist in the diagnosis of this species (
<bibRefCitation author="Holzenthal, R. W. &amp; Blahnik, R. J." box="[437,754,763,789]" pageId="3" pageNumber="581" pagination="1 - 37" refId="ref5850" refString="Holzenthal, R. W. &amp; Blahnik, R. J. (2006) The caddisfly genus Protoptila in Costa Rica (Trichoptera: Glossosomatidae). Zootaxa, 1197, 1 - 37." type="journal article" year="2006">Holzenthal &amp; Blahnik 2006</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
